	<clause id="uncertainty_analysis" obligation="normative"><title>Uncertainty Analysis</title><clause id="_categorising_the_uncertainty_components" obligation="normative"><title>Categorising the Uncertainty Components</title><p id="_1a7ace47-c334-4b8a-a47c-99b9b1416606">For the purposes of this report, the uncertainty components are separated into four categories, as shown in <xref target="fig5"/>. The main split is between those sources of uncertainty that are due to the calibration of the filter radiometer and those that are due to its use in measuring a blackbody. Some sources of uncertainty for the filter radiometer calibration are common to all four calibration schemes (<xref target="common_sources"/>), while others are specific to one scheme. The sources of uncertainty relating to the measurement of a blackbody can themselves be split into those due to the source and those due to the filter radiometer.</p>
