	<annex id="appendixA" obligation="informative"><title>Uncertainty Propagation Based on the Integral</title><clause id="appendixA-1" obligation="informative"><title>Concepts</title><p id="_4af74b54-4209-4205-a81f-2318d16943a9">The method of propagating uncertainties directly through the integral in <xref target="eq13"/> is described in detail in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="woolliams2014" citeas="[70]"/> and has also been published in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="yoon2003" citeas="[52]"/>, <eref type="inline" bibitemid="woolliams2003" citeas="[71]"/>, <eref type="inline" bibitemid="woolliams2006" citeas="[72]"/>. This method calculates the sensitivity coefficients in terms of signal directly from the practical numerical implementation of <xref target="eq13"/>, and uses implicit differentiation to convert these into sensitivity coefficients in terms of temperature.</p>
	<p id="_12c7b4cd-0fdb-4d16-a787-6c8b9f0ac4a5">In practice, <xref target="eq13"/> is solved by introducing the numerical summation (trapezium rule):</p>
	<formula id="eq77">
	<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>S</mi></mstyle></mrow></mtd><mtd><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>K</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced open="[" close="]"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>b</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><munderover><mrow><mo>∑</mo></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>N</mi></mstyle><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow></munderover><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>b</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>N</mi></mstyle></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mr